Home

Stop cycling, start cruisin’

Looks good,
rides even better

   The relatively thick tires and stiff frame make it a perfect bike for a
   comfortable ride. We don’t expect you will ride your Sandwichbike
   indoors, so we made sure the wooden frame will do its job, rain or
   shine.

   sandwichbikes-awards-2014 sandwichbikes-awards-2015
   [sandwichbikes-home-back.png]

   [sandwichbikes-home-assembling.png]

Build it yourself, make it your own

   Besides producing a bicycle made out of sustainable materials, we also
   wanted to encourage sustainable use. By letting people assemble their
   Sandwichbike themselves, we want to let them see how beautifully the
   materials are made and come together. Engaging people this way creates
   a unique experience.

Sustainable design

   The wooden frame that is harvested in a sustainable managed forest in
   Germany, gives each frame its own unique identity. Building, designing
   and constantly innovating Sandwichbikes gives us a deep thrill that we
   would like everyone to have when assembling their Sandwichbikes.
   [sandwichbikes-home-handlebar.png]

